you see any transfer?

00:40:12.420 --> 00:40:14.300
Or do you see any different
interpretations

00:40:14.300 --> 00:40:17.710
in West Germany compared to how
the East Germans are taking this

00:40:17.710 --> 00:40:23.190
as a means of sort of
rebellion against authority?

00:40:23.190 --> 00:40:24.630
&gt;&gt; Leonard Schmieding:
It's a good question.

00:40:24.630 --> 00:40:29.340
If you look at how hip-hop
got into West Germany,

00:40:29.340 --> 00:40:33.570
was by African-American
GIs and the military bases,

00:40:33.570 --> 00:40:37.970
the American military bases play
the most important role in this.

00:40:37.970 --> 00:40:42.740
And so young teenagers from West
Germany could actually meet these

00:40:42.740 --> 00:40:45.460
GIs in the clubs, and they
would bring the records,

00:40:45.460 --> 00:40:48.450
they would bring the know-how,
and they knew how to dress well

00:40:48.450 --> 00:40:49.920
as a hip-hopper and
so on and so forth.

00:40:49.920 --> 00:40:57.110
So you had this is the main
kind of I guess contrast, right,

00:40:57.110 --> 00:41:00.180
main difference between
these two scenes.

00:41:00.180 --> 00:41:08.220
I think that due to the fact
that hip-hop in the GDR was kind

00:41:08.220 --> 00:41:12.240
of was transported by
already a stereotype, right.

00:41:12.240 --> 00:41:18.110
Because "Beat Street" was basically
not received very well even in 1984

00:41:18.110 --> 00:41:21.690
in the United States, because
it was already deemed dead.

00:41:21.690 --> 00:41:25.190
With the recording industry
and record industry,

00:41:25.190 --> 00:41:27.500
they basically already had
exported hip-hop enough

00:41:27.500 --> 00:41:29.360
and it was drained of its soul.

00:41:29.360 --> 00:41:33.990
So everything that could then
be exported was not the real

00:41:33.990 --> 00:41:35.290
thing anymore.

00:41:35.290 --> 00:41:38.440
And "Beat Street" conveyed
that in a sense.

00:41:38.440 --> 00:41:44.500
And it's not taking place in its
original place, it's Queens, right,

00:41:44.500 --> 00:41:48.920
and not the Bronx, where
they shot the movie.

00:41:48.920 --> 00:41:56.270 position:56%
But the GIs, they were real like
disc jockeys, or they had knowledge,

00:41:56.270 --> 00:41:58.860
and I guess they showed
it and they shared it.

00:41:58.860 --> 00:42:03.160
And I guess the way of looking
at African-Americans in East

00:42:03.160 --> 00:42:05.380
and West is different this way.

00:42:05.380 --> 00:42:14.420
And in terms of rebellion,
I think it's worth noticing

00:42:14.420 --> 00:42:17.830
that in West Germany,

00:42:17.830 --> 00:42:24.940
African-American GIs barely had
a public space due to the racism

00:42:24.940 --> 00:42:27.530
within the Armed Forces,
American Armed Forces,

00:42:27.530 --> 00:42:29.790
but also in West Germany society.

00:42:29.790 --> 00:42:31.580
And they kind of built a coalition

00:42:31.580 --> 00:42:34.570
with the immigrants
Turks population.

00:42:34.570 --> 00:42:39.600
So Funkadelic, the first and for
a long time only black music club

00:42:39.600 --> 00:42:42.930
in Frankfurt, in West Germany, very
close to all of the American bases,

00:42:42.930 --> 00:42:47.360
of course, was run by a young Turk.

00:42:47.360 --> 00:42:50.320
So I guess you had
minority populations

00:42:50.320 --> 00:42:52.520
and they joined forces somehow.

00:42:52.520 --> 00:42:56.590
And in East Germany, you
didn't have it that much.

00:42:56.590 --> 00:43:01.650
I mean, you had African contract
workers from Angola, Mozambique,

00:43:01.650 --> 00:43:06.810
and sometimes also Cuba, and
they were very like attractive

00:43:06.810 --> 00:43:10.090
for the young B-Boys because they
would bring some authenticity

00:43:10.090 --> 00:43:14.230
to the breakdance crews, which
is highly problematic, of course.

00:43:14.230 --> 00:43:19.150
But they were ghettoized in
the GDR by the regime already.

00:43:19.150 --> 00:43:20.910
They could only live
in certain cities,

00:43:20.910 --> 00:43:22.910
in certain dwellings,
and so on and so forth.

00:43:22.910 --> 00:43:26.930
But they kind of made it out there
sometimes and then intermingled

00:43:26.930 --> 00:43:31.470
but not in a way that it
happened in West Germany.

00:43:31.470 --> 00:43:34.540
And I guess West Germany
was more commercialized

00:43:34.540 --> 00:43:38.030
from the very beginning because
you could just buy Nike and Puma,

00:43:38.030 --> 00:43:40.340
Adidas wear, and you
could buy all the records.

00:43:40.340 --> 00:43:43.280
And in the GDR, you had to be
a little bit more inventive

00:43:43.280 --> 00:43:44.970
and you had to improvise more.

00:43:44.970 --> 00:43:48.190
So that's the main
differences, and also I think

00:43:48.190 --> 00:43:53.310
that speaks a little bit about
the potential of rebellion.

